# {{ cookiecutter.project_name }} — frontend (React + Vite + Radix Themes)

> Generated by [`django-bakery`](https://github.com/Axionore/Django-Barkery). React 19 · Vite 7 · TypeScript 6 · Radix Themes · React Router v7.

The frontend is an SPA wired to the Django backend via **session cookies**. There is no JWT in localStorage, no token in JS, no Authorization header — Django's `sessionid` cookie (HttpOnly, SameSite=Lax) is the only credential, and Django's `csrftoken` cookie (read by JS) lands in the `X-CSRFToken` header on every mutating request.

## Quickstart

```bash
# from the project root
pnpm install                  # workspace install — covers backend+frontend
pnpm --filter frontend dev    # vite dev server on http://localhost:{{ cookiecutter.frontend_dev_port }}

# OR via docker compose (preferred — runs Django + Postgres + Mailpit too)
docker compose -f compose.local.yml up
```

The Vite dev server proxies `/api`, `/_allauth`, `/static`, `/media` to Django on `:8000`, so cookies stay first-party and CSRF works without CORS gymnastics.

