## Authentication contract

The SPA talks to `django-allauth`'s **headless** API at `/_allauth/browser/v1/...`. See `apps/users/middleware.py` for the staff-MFA enforcement layer.

Login flow (most-common branches):

```
POST /_allauth/browser/v1/auth/login                  { email, password }
  200 → user is signed in ({ data.user })
  401 + flows[].id === "mfa_authenticate" → MFA challenge
  401 + flows[].id === "verify_email" → user must verify email first
  401 (no flows) → invalid credentials
  429 → too many attempts (allauth's built-in rate limit)
```

The auth client (`src/auth/client.ts`) returns an exhaustive Result type so the caller can't accidentally drop a branch.

### Why session cookies and not JWTs?

Storing tokens in `localStorage` is an OWASP A02 anti-pattern — any XSS becomes total account takeover. With Django's session cookies:
- `sessionid` is `HttpOnly` — XSS cannot read it.
- `SameSite=Lax` blocks cross-site cookie forwarding.
- The CSRF token is the only cookie JS reads, and it's only useful in a same-site context.

If you NEED a JWT (e.g. for a mobile app calling the same API), use [`django-ninja-jwt`](https://django-ninja.dev/guides/authentication/#django-ninja-jwt) (Ninja) or [SimpleJWT](https://django-rest-framework-simplejwt.readthedocs.io/) (DRF) at a separate `/api/token/*` namespace — never mix the two on the same route.

## Calling the typed API

{% if cookiecutter.api_layer == 'ninja' %}
The backend uses **Django Ninja**. The auth model in the generated `apps/api/ninja_api.py` is `django_auth` (session-based) — see [django-ninja auth docs](https://django-ninja.dev/guides/authentication/). To call an endpoint from React:

```ts
import { fetchMe } from "~/api/client";

const me = await fetchMe();   // sessionid cookie forwarded automatically
```

Regenerate the TypeScript types whenever the backend schema changes:

```bash
pnpm openapi:gen
```
{% elif cookiecutter.api_layer == 'drf' %}
The backend uses **DRF**. The auth classes (in `config/settings/base.py`) are `SessionAuthentication` + `TokenAuthentication` — see [DRF auth docs](https://www.django-rest-framework.org/api-guide/authentication/). For the SPA, SessionAuthentication is the path: the same session cookie set by allauth carries forward.

Regenerate the OpenAPI-driven types:

```bash
pnpm openapi:gen
```
