This project chose `api_layer = {{ cookiecutter.api_layer }}` — see the project README for the relevant client docs.
{% endif %}

## Theming

`@radix-ui/themes` is configured in `src/main.tsx`. Adjust accent color, gray scale, radius, and scaling there. Dark mode is opt-in via `src/ui/theme.tsx` (toggle in the nav; persists in `localStorage`; first visit respects `prefers-color-scheme`).

To switch to **Radix Primitives + Tailwind v4** flavor, re-run `django-bakery new` with `radix_flavor = "primitives"` — a separate template tree ships instead of Themes.

## Security baseline (what's already on)

- Every fetch uses `credentials: "include"` — required for the session cookie.
- Every mutating fetch sends `X-CSRFToken` automatically (via `auth/csrf.ts`).
- Strict CSP (`script-src 'self'`) — extend `connect-src` if you add a third-party API.
- No raw HTML injection paths — `react/no-danger` ESLint rule.
- Source maps disabled in production builds.
- Sentry SDK (when `use_sentry=true`) strips Cookie / Authorization / X-CSRFToken from every event.

## Bundle-size budget

The main chunk is kept under **250 KB gzipped** (see `vite.config.ts` `chunkSizeWarningLimit`). React + React-Router + Radix Themes + zustand land at ~180 KB on a clean build — leaving headroom for project code.
